# A spread inside a cond-attr branch, combined with a top-level forwarding
# spread, is a second spread on the element (the at-most-one-spread count
# descends into cond-attr branches, issue #78): rejected because the
# conditional spread's keys are statically unknown, so merging it into the
# other spread would silently drop the { if } guard. The diagnostic is
# conditional-aware: it anchors on the nested spread and recommends building
# a gsx.AttrsCond bag instead of the generic .Merge() hint (which is reserved
# for two top-level spreads, see two_spreads_error.txtar).
-- input.gsx --
package views

import "github.com/gsxhq/gsx"

component Box(active bool, extra gsx.Attrs) {
	<div { if active { { extra... } } } { attrs... }>x</div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
6:21: a spread inside { if } ({ extra... }) has statically unknown keys and cannot be merged with another spread on the same element; build it as a conditional bag with gsx.AttrsCond(active, func() (gsx.Attrs, error) { return extra, nil }, nil) in a {{ }} block, then spread the merged result
